{"lemma":"أَبْرَشانِ","slug":"أَبْرَشانِ","root":"ب.ر.ش","root_slug":"ب-ر-ش","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ر-ش","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2276","n2280"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"dappled, mottled"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ب ر ش (b r š)."},"ipa":["/ʔab.raʃ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2276","headword_ar":"ابرشّ","root":"br$","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibor$aA$N","text_ar":"اـِبْرشَاشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a horse)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, marked with small specks, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bara$","text_ar":"بَرَش"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"differing from the rest of his colour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2280","headword_ar":"اَبْرَشُ","root":"br$","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a horse, (S, K,) or to one of the sort termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biro*awn","text_ar":"بِرْذَون"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Marked with the small speaks termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bara$","text_ar":"بَرَش"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariy$N","text_ar":"بَرِيشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) Also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN baro$aA='u","text_ar":"شَاةٌ بَرْشَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A ewe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she-goat, marked with specks of various colours."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~apN","text_ar":"حَيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baro$aA='u","text_ar":"بَرْشَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A serpent black speckled with white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white speckled with black."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraSu","text_ar":"اَبْرَصُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baro$aA='u","text_ar":"بَرْشَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buro$N","text_ar":"بُرْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) [or rather, used allusively for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraSu","text_ar":"اَبْرَصُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for] Jedheemeh (S, A, K) Ibn-Málik (S, TA) Ibn-Fahm, (TA,) the king [of El-Heereh], (K,) was surnamed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abora$u","text_ar":"الاَبْرَشُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in allusion to his being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraS","text_ar":"اَبْرَص"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, K;) the Arabs fearing to apply to him this latter epithet: (K:) or he was thus called because he was marked with black or red specks caused by a burn. (Kh.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAnN A^abora$u","text_ar":"مَكَانٌ اَبْرَشُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of various colours, abounding in plants"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN baro$aA='N","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ بَرْشَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sanapN baro$aA='u","text_ar":"سَنَةٌ بَرْشَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a year, in which is abundance of herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of various colours;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabo$aA='u","text_ar":"رَبْشَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramo$aA='u","text_ar":"رَمْشَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Lh","Msb","A","TA","Ks"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A3%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%B4/","headword_ar":"أبرشهر","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_12","lexicon_en":"Al-Muṭarrizī, al-Mughrib fī Tartīb al-Muʿrib (d. 1213 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المغرب في ترتيب المعرب للمُطَرِّزي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22029#6819ce","body_html":"نَافِعُ مَوْلَى ابْنِ عُمَرَ - رَضِيَ اللَّهُ عَنْهُمَا - كَانَ مِنْ (أبرشهر) هُوَ اسْمُ مَوْضِعٍ."}]}}